The historic Komani town hall in the Eastern Cape has gone up in flames. It's where the Enoch Mgijima local council sits. eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Komani Town Hall in the Eastern Cape has been mysteriously torched. This is the home of the Enoch Mgijima local municipality council which is regarded as a historical site in the area. READ: UPDATE: Old Assembly building on fire The building caught fire on Saturday morning. Community members lent a helping hand to put out the fire. It is alleged that the fire services responding to the blaze was inadequate.